

The spiral is the usual Ulam spiral  

\[
\begin{array}{ccc}
5&4&3\\
6&1&2\\
7&8&9
\end{array}
\]

with the centre at \((0,0)\) (the number 1).  
A number \(N\) is on the “layer’’  

\[
k=\Big\lceil\frac{\sqrt N-1}{2}\Big\rceil ,
\qquad
\text{max}(k)=(2k+1)^2,\;
\min (k)=(2k-1)^2+1 .
\]

---

### 1.  Locate 2026

\[
\sqrt{2026}\approx45.01,\qquad 
k=\Big\lceil\frac{45.01-1}{2}\Big\rceil =23 .
\]

Thus 2026 is the first number of layer 23.  
For a layer‑starting point we have  

\[
(x,y)=\big(k,\,-k+1\big)=(23,-22).
\]

---

### 2.  The eight neighbours

All neighbours of a point \((x,y)\) are the squares with coordinates  

\[
(x\pm1,y),\ (x,y\pm1),\ (x\pm1,y\pm1).
\]

Hence for \((23,-22)\) the neighbours are

| coordinate | layer | value |
|------------|-------|-------|
| (22,-22)   | 22    | \((2\cdot22+1)^2=2025\) |
| (22,-21)   | 22    | \((2\cdot22-3)^2+1=1850\) |
| (23,-21)   | 23    | \((2\cdot23-1)^2+1+1=2027\) |
| (23,-23)   | 23    | \((2\cdot23+1)^2=2209\) |
| (24,-23)   | 24    | \((2\cdot24-1)^2+1=2210\) |
| (24,-22)   | 24    | \(2210+1=2211\) |
| (24,-21)   | 24    | \(2210+2=2212\) |
| (22,-23)   | 23    | \(2209-1=2208\) |

(The numbers are obtained from the standard formulas for a point on a given side of a square layer; e.g. a point on the right side of layer \(k\) has value
\((2k-1)^2+1+(y+k-1)\), etc.)

---

### 3.  Summation

\[
\begin{aligned}
S&=2025+1850+2027+2209+2210+2211+2212+2208\\
  &=16952 .
\end{aligned}
\]

---

### 4.  (A quick check)

For the first number of any layer \(k\;(k\ge2)\) the eight neighbours sum to

\[
S=32k^{2}+24 .
\]

With \(k=23\),

\[
S=32\cdot 23^{2}+24=32\cdot529+24=16928+24=16952,
\]

the same result obtained above.

---

\[
\boxed{16952}
\]
